  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In this study, a functional evaluation of total knee arthroplasty (TKA) patients is
      performed. The patients are measured prior to surgery and 6 and 12 months after surgery. The
      measurements consist of questionnaires and rising from a chair. Also, two types of TKA are
      functionally evaluated. At last, the TKA group will be compared to a THP group.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
